modules.description: Handles when to print output in expectation tests using the `Always`, `If_unclean_exit`, and `Never` rules. Converts these print rules to S-expressions for serialization. Useful for controlling test output behavior in asynchronous code contexts.

This module provides functions for managing temporary directories, environment variables, and subprocess execution in asynchronous expectation tests. It supports operations like creating temporary directories, setting environment variables, and running external commands with captured output, all while handling asynchronous deferred results. Use cases include testing file system interactions, environment-dependent logic, and command-line tool integrations within async test contexts.
